title: THE BURNS and ALLEN SHOW -- The Switchboard Operator
description:
This third show of the Seventh Season was the final New York episode
(even though it was ALWAYS produced in Hollywood) and the 
last Burns & Allen Show produced by Fred de Cordova, who was replaced 
the following week by Rod Amateau for the rest of the series. 
Unfortunately I don't have "Return to California", in which the 
Burns and Mortons seemed to have have moved into new houses. 
Of course Harry Von Zell again made the move with them.
